NAME
    Data::DPath - DPath is not XPath!

SYNOPSIS
        use Data::DPath 'dpath';
        my $data  = {
                     AAA  => { BBB => { CCC  => [ qw/ XXX YYY ZZZ / ] },
                               RRR => { CCC  => [ qw/ RR1 RR2 RR3 / ] },
                               DDD => { EEE  => [ qw/ uuu vvv www / ] },
                             },
                    };
        @resultlist = dpath('/AAA/BBB/CCC')->match($data);
        ( ['XXX', 'YYY', 'ZZZ'] )
        @resultlist = dpath('/AAA/*/CCC')->match($data);
        # ( ['XXX', 'YYY', 'ZZZ'], [ 'RR1', 'RR2', 'RR3' ] )
        @resultlist = dpath('/AAA/BBB/CCC/../../DDD')->match($data);
        ( { EEE => [ qw/ uuu vvv www / ] } )

    See currently working paths in t/data_dpath.t.

INSTALLATION
     perl Makefile.PL
     make
     make test
     make install

FUNCTIONS
  dpath
    Meant as the front end function for everyday use of Data::DPath. It
    takes a path string and returns a Data::DPath::Path object for which
    smart matching ("~~") is overloaded. See SYNOPSIS.

METHODS
  match($data, $path)
    Returns all values in data that match the path as an array.

  get_context($path)
    Returns a Data::DPath::Context object that matches the path and can be
    used to incrementally dig into it.

